Hong Kong shares started the week with small gains on Monday, brushing off worries about the brewing US-Iran crisis to focus on upcoming talks between Donald Trump and Xi Jinping. The Hang Seng Index added 0.14% to 28 513.00. The benchmark Shanghai Composite Index added 0.21% to 3 008.15 but the Shenzhen Composite Index, which tracks stocks on China's second exchange, dipped 0.09% to 1 576.09. 